body:
I get an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException when using a color markup with a custom font generated by FreeTypeFont. This only seems to happen when the text in my text field is => 17 characters long. 
I've tried 3 other fonts and the problem persists, although it goes away if I use the default font shipped with LibGDX. Perhaps it's a FreeTypeFont issue? Looking at the stack trace, maybe it incorrectly determines offsets?

My version of LibGDX is 1.9.4 with FreeTypeFont extension. Stacktrace & ApplicationListener below.

```
public class ErrorTest implements ApplicationListener {

    @Override
    public void create() {
        TextFieldStyle style = new TextFieldStyle();
        /*
         * Change this font to a font generated by FreeTypeFont
         * and it seems to crash, although normal font works fine.
         */
        BitmapFont font = new BitmapFont();
        font.getData().markupEnabled = true;
        style.font = font;
        TextField textField = new TextField("", style);
        /* Crash here */
        textField.setText("[LIGHT_GREY] total text longer than 17 letters.");
    }

    @Override
    public void resize(int width, int height) {
    }

    @Override
    public void render() {
    }

    @Override
    public void pause() {
    }

    @Override
    public void resume() {
    }

    @Override
    public void dispose() {
    }

}
```

